Source: R/wafregional_operations.R
wafregional_get_web_acl.Rd

This is AWS WAF Classic documentation. For more information, see AWS WAF Classic in the developer guide.

For the latest version of AWS WAF, use the AWS WAFV2 API and see the AWS WAF Developer Guide. With the latest version, AWS WAF has a single set of endpoints for regional and global use.

Returns the WebACL that is specified by WebACLId.

wafregional_get_web_acl(WebACLId)

Arguments

WebACLId

[required] The WebACLId of the WebACL that you want to get. WebACLId is returned by create_web_acl and by list_web_ac_ls.

Value

A list with the following syntax:

list(
  WebACL = list(
    WebACLId = "string",
    Name = "string",
    MetricName = "string",
    DefaultAction = list(
      Type = "BLOCK"|"ALLOW"|"COUNT"
    ),
    Rules = list(
      list(
        Priority = 123,
        RuleId = "string",
        Action = list(
          Type = "BLOCK"|"ALLOW"|"COUNT"
        ),
        OverrideAction = list(
          Type = "NONE"|"COUNT"
        ),
        Type = "REGULAR"|"RATE_BASED"|"GROUP",
        ExcludedRules = list(
          list(
            RuleId = "string"
          )
        )
      )
    ),
    WebACLArn = "string"
  )
)

Request syntax

svc$get_web_acl(
  WebACLId = "string"
)

Examples

if (FALSE) {
# The following example returns the details of a web ACL with the ID
# createwebacl-1472061481310.
svc$get_web_acl(
  WebACLId = "createwebacl-1472061481310"
)
}
